```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "posets",
    "account": "use320",
    "partition": "gpu-shared",
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks_per_node": 6,
    "gpu": 1,
    "time": "00:30:00",
    "output": "poset.o%j.%N",
    "modules": "module purge",
    "environment": "printenv",
    "python_script": "spectrum.py"
  }
}
```

This script is running on **Slurm**, a workload manager for high-performance computing systems. 

Here are the details of the script:

* **Job Name**: "posets"
* **Account**: "use320"
* **Partition**: "gpu-shared"
* **Nodes**: 1 (meaning it will run on a single node of the compute cluster)
* **Tasks per Node**: 6 (meaning it will launch 6 processes on the single node)
* **GPU**: 1 (meaning it requires one GPU for execution)
* **Time**: "00:30:00" (meaning the job is allowed to run for a maximum of 30 minutes)
* **Output**: "poset.o%j.%N" (specifies the output file name for the job)
* **Modules**: The script purges all currently loaded modules and lists available modules.
* **Environment**: The script prints the environment variables currently set.
* **Python Script**: The script executes the "spectrum.py" Python script.
